<HEADLINE>
FT  18 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Copper highly volatile - Market
Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COPPER fluctuated wildly on the London Metal Exchange yesterday, reaching
Dollars 2,520 a tonne at one stage before closing Dollars 5 down from Friday
at Dollars 2,476.50. There was a Dollars 5 a tonne premium for metal for
immediate delivery compared with three-month aluminium at the close and that
backwardation (premium) reached a notional Dollars 50 at one point. Traders
said the bulk of the activity reflected 'third Wednesday' pricing and
trading, and covering against nearby option commitments. Big cash purchases
defended the Dollars 2,500 level in the morning before heavy Far Eastern
selling and fund liquidation established the lower trend, they said.
ALUMINIUM prices reached a new four-year high of Dollars 1,720 a tonne
before closing at Dollars 1,715.50, up Dollars 7.75.
Compiled from Reuters
