<HEADLINE>
FT  18 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Acquisitive MY leaps to Pounds 4.5m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WOLFFE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MY Holdings, the packaging group, pledged to continue its acquisitions
strategy after announcing an 80 per cent rise in pre-tax profits for the
year to August 27.
The company, which spent Pounds 23.3m acquiring four packaging businesses
this year, increased pre-tax profits from Pounds 2.51m to Pounds 4.51m on
turnover up 46 per cent to Pounds 51.2m (Pounds 35.1m).
Mr John Monks, chief executive, said the company was considering another
share issue to fund acquisitions this year. In February, the group raised
about Pounds 23m through a placing which more than doubled its market
capitalisation.
'This year's acquisitions are not the end of the story. We are only at the
beginning,' he said.
'We like healthcare and would like further expansion in that sector. We are
also looking to continue our expansion of specialist corrugated activities,
and would like to fill in gaps in our geographical spread. We do not really
have anything in the Midlands and the west country, and the Scottish market
would be very interesting to us.'
However, the directors warned that operating margins, which increased from
7.6 to 9.4 per cent last year, would come under pressure from price rises
for its pulp and paper raw materials.
Turnover on continuing businesses rose by 13 per cent to Pounds 39.8m,
despite a poor performance by Trondex, the moulded cushion packaging
business.
Stripping out acquisitions, operating profit grew 12 per cent to Pounds 3m.
Interest costs increased from Pounds 164,000 to Pounds 301,000 as the group
raised its borrowing for cash acquisitions and capital investment. Gearing
rose from 4.2 to 16.3 per cent.
Earnings per share grew 16 per cent to 4.52p (3.91p), as the number of
shares doubled.
The board recommended a final dividend of 1.1p to make a total of 1.6p
(1.25p) for the year.
</TEXT>
