FT  18 OCT 94 / Oftel lifts curbs on Cellnet
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW ADONIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Oftel, the telecommunications regulator, has revoked restrictions on
Cellnet, the mobile phone network joint venture between British
Telecommunications and Securicor, pre-venting it from cross-subsidising its
service-provision business.
Mr Don Cruickshank, the director-general of Oftel, said that the
restrictions were 'no longer necessary' because of action taken by Cellnet.
Mr Cruickshank said, however, that he intended to continue monitoring mobile
phone network companies to ensure they provided no 'unfair cross-subsidy' to
their service provision subsidiaries, which would adversely affect
independent service providers.
