   BAGHDAD
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Iraq's People's Assembly yesterday gathered for an extraordinary, secret
session to approve the recognition of United Nations-demarcated borders with
Kuwait and the Gulf state's sovereignty - a fundamental UN Security Council
precondition for any moves towards the easing of sanctions. The
hastily-called meeting was expected to deliver an official recognition of
Kuwait's sovereignty and borders in the terms required by this weekend's
Security Council resolution, which called on Iraq to make the recognition
through 'full and formal constitutional procedures'.
