FT  17 OCT 94 / Observer: Sold short
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
No doubt the Italian stock exchange authorities, always eager to enhance the
bourse's standing within the international financial community, thought long
and hard before christening a new futures contract - based on the index of
leading Italian shares - the FIB 30.
If the product takes off, trading on the Italian futures market can then be
termed fibbing, with specialist Italian dealers affectionately known as
fibbers.
